Experiment 5: Create and Use a Pivot Table in Excel

1. Prepare Your Data:

Enter sample data in a table, for example:
| Product | Category  | Sales  | |---------|-----------|--------| | A       | Office    | 100    | | B       | Home      | 150    | | A       | Office    | 200    | | C       | Electronics | 300  |



2. Insert PivotTable:

Select your entire table.

Go to Insert > PivotTable.

Choose to place the PivotTable in a new worksheet and click OK.



3. Build the PivotTable:

Drag Product to the Rows area.

Drag Sales to the Values area.

To add a filter, drag Category into the Filters area.

(Optional) Use PivotTable Analyze > Insert Slicer for visual filtering.
